        "preparation": "\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E10 to 12 Hours of Overnight Fasting Is Mandatory\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E",
        "report": "24",
        "reporting": "All Day Available",
        "test_pre_test_info": "\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003EThe CityExtended Health Package, encompassing tests for calcium levels, diabetes screening, vitamin B12, and vitamin D25, provides a comprehensive and proactive approach to individual well-being. By addressing these key health markers, individuals can take informed steps toward maintaining optimal health and preventing potential health issues. Embracing such holistic health packages reflects a commitment to promoting a healthier and more resilient urban population. Regular screenings and proactive health management empower individuals to lead fulfilling lives in the bustling city environment.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Ch2\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECalcium Levels Test:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/h2\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003ECalcium is a vital mineral essential for bone health, muscle function, and nerve transmission. The calcium levels test included in the extended health package helps evaluate the adequacy of calcium in the body. Abnormalities in calcium levels can indicate conditions such as osteoporosis, hyperparathyroidism, or vitamin D deficiency. Early detection allows for timely intervention and the implementation of strategies to maintain optimal calcium levels.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Ch2\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetes Screening:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/h2\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003EDiabetes has become a global health concern, with a rising prevalence in urban populations. The extended health package includes comprehensive diabetes screening to assess blood glucose levels and identify potential insulin resistance. Early detection of diabetes or pre-diabetic conditions allows individuals to make lifestyle modifications, such as dietary changes and increased physical activity, to prevent or manage the disease effectively.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Ch2\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVitamin B12 Assessment:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/h2\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003EVitamin B12 plays a crucial role in maintaining nerve function, DNA synthesis, and the production of red blood cells. Deficiency in vitamin B12 can lead to fatigue, anemia, and neurological issues. The health package includes a test for vitamin B12 levels, enabling early identification of deficiencies. This information is valuable for guiding dietary changes or recommending supplements to ensure optimal vitamin B12 levels.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Ch2\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVitamin D25 Test:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/h2\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003EVitamin D is essential for bone health, immune function, and overall well-being. The extended health package incorporates a test for vitamin D25, which measures the level of active vitamin D in the body. Inadequate vitamin D levels are associated with various health issues, including bone disorders and compromised immune function. Early detection allows for interventions such as sunlight exposure, dietary changes, or supplementation to address deficiencies.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E",
        "test_type": "Package",
        "test_components": "\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECalcium (1 Test):-\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:15px;\"\u003E Calcium\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetes Screening (2 Tests):-\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:15px;\"\u003E Glucose Fasting, HBA1C\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKFT / RFT (8 Tests):-\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:15px;\"\u003E Blood Urea, Creatinine, Uric Acid, Total Protein, Albumin, Globulin, A/G Ratio, Blood Urea Nitrogen\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELipid Profile (7 Tests):-\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:15px;\"\u003E Cholesterol, Triglyceride, HDL-Cholesterol, VLDL, Total Cholesterol/HDL Ratio, LDL Cholesterol, LDL/HDL Ratio\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELiver Function Test(LFT) (11 Tests):-\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:15px;\"\u003E Total Protein, Albumin, Globulin, A/G Ratio, SGOT (AST), SGPT (ALT), Alkaline Phosphatase, Total Bilirubin, Conjugated Bilirubin, Unconjugated Bilirubin (Indirect), Gamma G.T.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERoutine Urine Examination (17 Tests):-\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:15px;\"\u003E Colour, Transparency, Specific Gravity, PH, Urine Albumin, Ketones, Glucose, Leucocyte Esterase, Nitrite, Blood, Pus Cells, R.B.C, Casts, Crystals, Epithelial Cells, Yeast Cells, Others\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECBC, Complete Blood Count (25 Tests):-\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:15px;\"\u003E Haemoglobin, TLC (Total Leucocyte Count), Neutrophil, Lymphocytes, Monocytes, Eosinophil, Basophils, RBC, PCV/Haematocrit, MCV, MCH, MCHC, Platelet Count, Absolute Neutrophil Count, Absolute Lymphocyte Count, Absolute Monocyte Count, Absolute Eosinophil Count, Absolute Basophil Count, RDW-CV, RDW SD, PDW, MPV, P-LCR, PCT, IG\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThyroid Profile (3 Tests):-\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:15px;\"\u003E T3, T4, TSH (Ultra Sensitive)\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVitamin B12 (1 Tests):- \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:15px;\"\u003EVitamin B12 Level\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:16px;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVitamin D25 (1 Tests):-\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-size:15px;\"\u003E Vitamin D Total (25 Oh) Cholecalciferol\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E",
